<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 4:58PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A line of gusty showers will impact portions of southeastern
Kanawha, southwestern Clay, northwestern Fayette and northeastern
Boone Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 453 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of gusty showers
from Clendenin southwest to Racine, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Montgomery, Chesapeake, Marmet, Belle, Cedar Grove, East Bank,
Glasgow, Smithers, Pratt, Burnwell, Powellton, Glen, Coal Fork,
Handley, Seth, Leewood, Dawes, Indore, Sharon and Eskdale.
This includes West Virginia Turnpike between mile markers 65 and 90.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
